jobdescription: CarServ is seeking a senior full-stack developer to contribute to our Ruby on Rails and Angular (v8) applications.  Why work at CarServ?CarServ is overhauling the automotive repair experience with our innovative software.  Our operating system provides an end-to-end software solution that allows automotive service centers to cut costs, improve efficiency, and maximize customer satisfaction.  CarServ is a Techstars Austin 2016 alum and is backed by Salesforce Ventures.  We are also an official partner of Lyft. Watch our winning 2018 Salesforce Dreampitch to learn more about our company and platform at https://youtu.be/OnF8MCkwcHQ?t=1822.  Our goal is to be inclusive in this search, and truly welcome people from different backgrounds and perspectives into the process. Responsibilities and OpportunitiesAssume these responsibilities represent the floor, not the ceiling. Were interested in your ideas once youre on board.- Optimize and improve existing Ruby on Rails and Angular (v8) applications.- Collaborate on defining requirements and implementing new features.- Lead implementation of new feature areas and coach junior developers.- Ensure existing and new features are well-documented and have full test coverage.- Participate in sprint planning, budgeting and code reviews, sometimes taking the lead.Required Skills And Experience- 3+ years experience building enterprise grade API-driven applications.- Experience collaborating with a team of developers, including remote team members.- Ability to write clean, well-documented code and test coverage.- Strong experience with Ruby on Rails and JavaScript MVC frameworks.- Experience with TypeScript and Angular 2+.- Passion for creating great user experiences.- Experience working with SQL databases.Our Values: Work hard, work smart. Be kind and candid with each other. Exercise empathy in building both our product and our company.  We are solving a big problem and we need a diverse, thoughtful, engaged and determined team to do it!How to ApplyPlease email your resume along with a brief note explaining your interest in becoming a full-stack engineer at CarServ to jobs@carserv.com.  We will invite candidates to interview on a rolling basis.CompensationWe believe in rewarding talent!  CarServ offers competitive salary, equity, PTO and benefits to all employees.In ClosingWe want to meet a broad set of candidates and run an inclusive process. If something here prompts a question or concern for you, please contact us at jobs@carserv.com to share your feedback. Thanks for your interest in joining the CarServ team!
skills: Javascript, PostgreSQL, Agile Methodologies, Ruby on Rails, TypeScript, Angular

jobdescription: We are seeking an ambitious software developer with strong industry skills to join our rapidly growing team in developing tools and software for both internal use and as a service to customers in the power generation industry. We are a highly-motivated, fun-loving team that holds ourselves to a very high standard. The successful candidate will have an immediate impact, and will contribute to a positive, productive and fun workplace.Our environment is moving towards a cloud-based containerized system with a heavy focus on Python-driven web based services that are integrated with our ERP/accounting system. Experience with Python is highly valued, and familiarity with Docker, web development (html/javascript/node.js) and accounting/ERP systems is an asset.We are a relatively new development team, so this opportunity provides a wide horizon of future possibilities. The successful candidate will have a major impact on the direction of the organization, participating in decisions as to which opportunities to pursue and which strategies are employed to grow the team and the business.Responsibilities (will vary with skillset):  Design, build and maintain tools that increase the efficiency of work flows and improve communication of our staff.   Design & build software, APIs and services for our customers, following best practices to ensure relatively bug-free deployments. Gather data programmatically from industrial meters, sensors and controllers via standard protocols (eg. Modbus over TCP/IP)  Design and maintain relational databases and develop tools and APIs to help end-users interact with data. Write unit tests for new and existing code and strive towards full test coverage  Write and maintain internal and end-user documentation for new and existing projects. Work with IT, accounting, service, sales and production teams to gather project requirements and set timelines.   Develop and maintain CI/CD pipelines using GitLab, Docker and AWS hosts.  Research, develop and implement development workflows and philosophiesRequirements Must have experience with at least one of:    Python (strongly preferred)   Javascript, node.js and html  ERP/accounting software development   Experience with databases (PostgreSQL, SQL Server, etc.). Strong analytical, troubleshooting and problem-solving skills.    Strong written and verbal communication skills.   Outstanding attention to detail.  Passion for learning new technologies, creating functional solutions and constantly improving.Preferred Skills and Experience   Experience with testing web and client/server applications.   Strong proficiency in automation and automated testing, including functional, integration, stress, performance, and other tests.  Experience with Docker and container based build infrastructures. Experience with git and CI/CD workflows   Experience with cloud systems (AWS, EC2, ECS).    Proven success in project management and software design would be an asset if seeking a senior role.  Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related discipline.    Experienced software developer (3+ years).And most importantly... YOU MUST be willing to have fun and be part of a fantastic team
